		c	For most particles, velocity works as expected.\nFor NoteParticle, velocityX is note number divided by 24, resulting in a scalar that affects color between 0 and 1. velocityY and velocityZ are ignored and always set to 0.\nFor RedDustParticle, velocityX, velocityY, and velocityZ are multipliers for the particle's color for red, green, and blue respectively.\n\n@see net.minecraft.client.particle.NoteParticle#NoteParticle(World, double, double, double, double, double, double, float)\n@see net.minecraft.client.particle.RedDustParticle#RedDustParticle(World, double, double, double, float, float, float, float)
